Even in death, they have their uses. They just need a little encouragement.
To me, brave companions! Feel my radiance flow through you!
Light and unadorned, like wind on water, you will be.
Why should I dodge blows that I do not fear?
Great tacticians learn that consistency often trumps potential.

Stand your ground, child, keep your senses.
The pain is fleeting, but victory is forever.
Give up everything in pursuit of greatness - even life itself.

What need have I for defence when my enemies
are reduced to ash and splinters?
Lay open your veins, and draw power from your own spilled life.
I give you everything, my pets. My trust, my strength, my safety. Do not disappoint me.

Embrace the pain, drink it in.
Your enemies will know your agony tenfold.
Balance is good in all things, but especially in the realm of magic.
Legend tells of bows so powerful that only giants could draw them back.
Look your foe in the eyes before you pierce him. Delight in his fear.
Let the whistling of arrows and stones be your music.

With enough practice, you can feel the spells
coming before they're even cast.

A wooden construct, mute and blind.
But fear the wrath of shackled mind.
I will wear your ghost, and you will die twice: against me, and for me.

only from the ravaged flesh of my enemies.

Burn the spirit to vitalise the flesh.
Utter trust in your defence unleashes ultimate potential.

Invite the enemy when you are strong, evade them when you are weak;
strike with the coming of the storm.
Put your faith in intellect rather than mysticism.

You are the heart of the empire, shining bright so that all are lifted up by your light.
Let none tell you otherwise.
